## 7. Assumptions

| ID | Assumption | Risk if Wrong |
|----|------------|---------------|
| A-001 | PostgreSQL (Neon) is the final database choice | Low — documented |
| A-002 | UUID is acceptable for all primary keys | Low — standard practice |
| A-003 | JSONB fields are acceptable for flexible metadata | Medium — may need structure later |
| A-004 | Soft deletes (status='deleted') are preferred over hard deletes | Low — industry standard |
| A-005 | Analytics can be derived from transactions (no real-time requirements) | Medium — may need streaming |
| A-006 | Single-region deployment initially | Medium — affects partitioning strategy |

